description:
This is a no-cable fix for Rocksmith 2014. You can now use a line in rather then an expensive real-tone cable to play Rocksmith 2014.

It works by changing addresses found by a user on the following thread; &lt;a href=&quot;
http://cs.rin.ru/forum/viewtopic.php?f=10&amp;t=63705&amp;start=1185&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://cs.rin.ru/forum/viewtopic.php?f=10&amp;t=63705&amp;start=1185&lt;/a&gt;
It was later automated and will dynamically change the required memory address.

Usage:
1. Download
2. Run Rocksmith
3. Go into the sound panel and disable all microphones but one
4. Ensure that the input is set to 16bit 48kHz
5. Play rocksmith.
-  You'll have to re-run the patch every time you launch Rocksmith


